FBIS3-1156 "drafr055_d_94009" FBIS-AFR-94-055 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Mar 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Mozambique Government, Renamo Soldiers To Join New Army MB2103191594 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 1730 GMT 21 Mar 94 MB2103191594 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] The government and the Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] had already selected 2,622 soldiers to join the future Mozambique Defense Armed Forces by 18 March. Of this number, 1,893 come from the government army, while the remaining 729 came from Renamo. The UN Operations in Mozambique daily report points out that by 18 March the government had demobilized 2,721 soldiers, while Renamo had demobilized 100 men. Radio Mozambique in Tete Province points out that 250 government soldiers were demobilized at the Xitima assembly area in Cahora Bassa District today.
